[SAY] The pattern `\s*=` finds any spaces before each equals sign. The replacement starts with `\=`, so Vim evaluates code instead of inserting literal text.
[SAY] `repeat(' ', 6-col('.'))` makes enough spaces to put the equals sign in column 6. Now pause, read it, then run it.
